	<content><![CDATA[const words = (str, pattern = /[^a-zA-Z-]+/) => str.split(pattern).filter(Boolean);]]></content>
	<description>Converts a given string into an array of words.  Use `String.split()` with a supplied pattern (defaults to non-alpha as a regexp) to convert to an array of strings. Use `Array.filter()` to remove any empty strings. Omit the second argument to use the default regexp.</description>
